This paper deals with the complexity of answering ontology-mediated queries in ontology-based data access, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of nonrecursive datalog (NDL) rewritings, which is a technique used in logic and knowledge representation (cs.LO). The paper also mentions the bounded treewidth of queries, which is a concept from graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of answering queries, which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
